'''Jorge Abdiel Gutiérrez Cornejo''' (born 1 September 1998) is a Panamanian football player who plays as [[left-back]] for [[Deportivo La Guaira F.C.|Deportivo La Guaira]], and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Career==
Gutiérrez began his senior career with the Panamanian club [[Tauro F.C.|Tauro]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bitacoradeportiva.com/2019/08/jorge-gutierrez-creo-que-vamos-a-tomar-el-camino-por-donde-deberiamos-ir/|title=Jorge Gutiérrez: "Creo que vamos a tomar el camino por donde deberíamos ir."|date=August 22, 2019}}</ref> For the 2020–21 season, he joined the Spanish club [[UD Melilla|Melilla]] on loan in the [[Primera División RFEF]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rpctv.com/futbol-nacional/jorge-gutierrez-habla-su-experiencia-espana-n5317943|title=Jorge Gutiérrez habla sobre su experiencia en España|website=www.rpctv.com}}</ref> On 28 December 2022, he transferred to the [[Venezuelan Primera División]] side [[Deportivo La Guaira F.C.|Deportivo La Guaira]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rpctv.com/futbol-internacional/futbol/jorge-gutierrez-es-presentado-como-nuevo-jugador-del-deportivo-la-guaira-n5823796|title=Jorge Gutiérrez es presentado como nuevo jugador del Deportivo La Guaira|website=www.rpctv.com}}</ref>

==International career==
Gutiérrez made his debut for the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]] in a 0-0 friendly tie with [[Peru national football team|Peru]] on 16 January 2022. After 3 years away, Gutierrez would return to the national team in 2025, playing huge roles in the [[2024-25 CONCACAF Nations League|CONCACAF nations league]], [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONCACAF)|World Cup qualifiers]] and [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup|gold cup]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/33069/Peru_Panama.html|title=Peru vs. Panama|first=Benjamin|last=Strack-Zimmermann|website=www.national-football-teams.com}}</ref>

